## Appendix: Critical Assessment Checklist

<!-- Run this against your PRD before starting implementation. Use /advise or do manually.
     Save results to: docs/plans/YYYY-MM-DD-prd-critical-assessment.md -->

**Ask these questions:**

| # | Check | What to Look For |
|---|-------|-----------------|
| 1 | **Consistency** | Do all docs (PRD, arch, SPEC) agree on terminology, data models, roles? |
| 2 | **Feasibility** | Can every feature be built with the stated stack within the stated timeline? |
| 3 | **Security** | Are there auth gaps, exposed data, missing RLS, credential risks? |
| 4 | **Cost reality** | Will free tiers last? Are API costs estimated correctly? |
| 5 | **Scale** | What breaks at 10x users? 100x data? |
| 6 | **Open questions** | Are any blocking questions unresolved for Phase 1? |
| 7 | **Boundaries** | Are ALWAYS/ASK/NEVER rules specific enough to enforce? |
| 8 | **Acceptance criteria** | Is every Phase 1 feature testable as written? |
